The paper deals with coding techniques for protecting against erasures and noise, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of frames and their properties also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the concept of side-information (SI) is relevant to source coding (cs.SI).
